<br>
First, is the one we have. All is peachy, the little blue and red prismatic dragon is asleep and warded.<br>
Second is the one after he left. It sucks/ed, and everyone on every server who awoke Kerafyrm griped because (rightly so, really), there was no good reason to awaken him, aside from the joy and entertainment of it wiping out all Skyshrine.  The only really new thing was a quest with an incredibly rare drop to do (on the scale of 2-3 ZONE clearings, to see one scale).<br>
<br>
Third, they revamped Skyshrine and Sleeper's Tomb on servers who woke him.  A new form of Primal Weaponry, the Ancient Prismatic was released, along with a few interesting drops that are actually decent if you're not VT/Elemental/Time level.  I don't know a whole lot beyond that about it, naturally, as I've played solely on FV since before this revamp.<br>
<br>
Edit-changing my opinion regarding Kerafyrm.<br>
<br>
Cons are: We lose our &quot;specialness&quot;, as there's probably half a dozen or less servers who still have it, I think Test does, we do, maybe a Zek server or two, but I think that's about it.  Competition for stuff to kill is FIERCE on other servers, since stuff takes only half an hour to find and assemble a force, if not less, a few minutes to kill, and days to reappear.<br>
<br>
We lose a few special items, such as Mask of the Tinkerers or some such, Sceptres of Destruction, and some monk robes I've never bothered looking at.<br>
<br>
*shrug*  That's about it in a nutshell<br>
